32:10.043 --> 32:22.385
Arlington, HARC, and we're trying to set up a 
project at UT Austin. And since we are a state

32:22.405 --> 32:25.030
organization,

32:26.663 --> 32:28.585
perfectly justified in doing that. In fact, it's 
recommended that we do. Now, this is one

32:31.068 --> 32:38.377
particular project you're working on, or a 
totally separate, affiliated in-vent project?

32:38.397 --> 32:54.156
Well, it would be an individual project that would 
be worked on there rather than here, mainly

32:38.397 --> 32:54.156
because the inventor's in Austin, and UT Austin 
has some people that are particularly talented in

32:38.397 --> 32:54.156
this particular field. and it would just make a 
great deal of sense to do it out there. And that's in

32:58.525 --> 33:04.893
the process of it, so.

